radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is visualized in the right lower quadrant, which appears fluid-filled and borderline dilated up to 7 mm in diameter with mild periappendiceal stranding and hyperenhancement of the wall. The lung bases are clear. No free air or free fluid is present. There are no focal liver lesions, no retroperitoneal or abdominal adenopathy, and the remainder of the bowel is normal. The bladder and prostate are normal. No concerning osteoblastic or osteolytic lesion identified.
